title: Moonlighting
description: The sly, hip, often imitated romantic dramedy about an ex-model and a PI who team up to run the Blue Moon Detective Agency. As the lead characters tried to decide if they loved or hated each other, the series established itself as a prime example of the `will they or won't they' subgenre so popular in 1980s TV. Filled with rapid-fire dialogue, in-jokes and some memorable parodies, this is a show, as its creator Glenn Gordon Caron said, `that knows it's on television.'

title: Crash
description: Characters of many ethnicities chase the American dream in Los Angeles in this drama adapted from the Oscar-winning Best Picture.
genres: Paul Haggis, Bobby Moresco, Bob Yari, Glen Mazzara

title: Richard Hammond's Crash Course
description: Crash courses in operating America's largest and most dangerous vehicles are undertaken.

title: Crashing
description: Comedy about a timid, aspiring comedian whose life is turned upside down by his wife's affair, forcing him into a nomadic existence to depend on the kindness of strangers for a roof over his head as he struggles to find his place in the chaotic New York stand-up scene.

title: Chicago Fire
description: A drama series following the firefighters, paramedics and rescue squad of Chicago Firehouse 51.
genres: Derek Haas, Michael Brandt, Matt Olmstead, Joe Chappelle, Dick Wolf, Danielle Gelber, Peter Jankowski

title: Chicago P.D.
description: A 'Chicago Fire' spin-off following the men and women of the Chicago Police Department.

title: Chicago Med
description: Hospital dramas play out in a state-of-the-art trauma center in this "Chicago Fire" spin-off, which delves into the lives of its doctors, nurses and staff.

title: Last Week Tonight With John Oliver
description: John Oliver's satirical look at the previous week's news, politics and headlines.

title: John Oliver's New York Stand-Up Show
description: "Daily Show" correspondent John Oliver hosts performances by his favorite comedians.

title: Jamie Oliver's Food Revolution
description: British chef Jamie Oliver tries to transform the eating habits of people in Huntington, W.V., which has been called the unhealthiest city in America, in this six-part reality series. His goal is to help Americans tackle obesity, heart disease and diabetes, by teaching people to eat more balanced meals and cook with fresh ingredients.
genres: Ryan Seacrest, Craig Armstrong, Adam J. Sher, Roy Ackerman, Adam Sher

title: Don't Trust the B---- in Apartment 23
description: An optimistic girl from the heartland moves to New York and is forced to live with a party girl who has "the morals of a pirate."

title: Wings
description: Sensible Joe Hackett and his fun-loving brother, Brian, run a one-plane airline in this folksy ensemble sitcom. Their mutual friend (and on-again, off-again love interest for Joe) is Helen, who works the lunch counter while dreaming of being a cellist. Among their quirky coworkers: a dim-bulb maintenance man and Tony Shalhoub's Italian-immigrant cabbie. The series was produced by the same folks responsible for 'Cheers' and had a nice seven-year run.
